A suspected rhino poacher has been trampled on by an elephant then eaten by lions in Kruger National Park, South Africa. Accomplice poachers told the victim’s family that he had been killed by an elephant on Tuesday. Relatives notified the park ranger. A search party struggled to find the body but eventually found a human skull and a pair of trousers on Thursday. The managing executive of the park extended his condolences to the family. How discovery of leopard is changing Yankari’s story SOUTH AFRICA: Lions eat ''rhino poachers'' on game reserve Yankari Game Reserve: Centre of attraction becomes distraction